desc=Barbarians are warriors born in savage lands, far from the mollifying comforts of civilization. Barbarians rely on hardiness, stealth, and foolhardy bravery to beat their enemies. Barbarians do not surprise as easily, and cannot be harmed by Thief's sneak attack, Scout's sniper shot or Assassin's death strike unless the thief/scout/assassin is of a higher level than the Barbarian. Barbarians gain additional Armor Class when fighting Unarmored, which rises with level gained, and deal twice strength damage when attacking with melee weapons. Barbarians may also add `rage` to their melee attacks, which gives an additional +2 to accuracy and damage, but reduces the Barbarian's AC by 2 until the start of his or her next turn. Barbarians also move 5 additional feet per round.//In order to qualify to be a Barbarian, a character requires a Strength of 9 or higher, a Dexterity of 9 or higher, and a Constitution of 9 or higher.//Barbarians may use leather armor, but no heavy armor, and may wield any weapon.

