desc=Paladins are divine warriors who fight in service of their deity or religious organization. To become a Paladin, a character must have at least a Strength of 9, a Wisdom of 11, and a Charisma of 11. There are no racial restrictions for the Paladin. Paladins may use any weapon and wear any armor or shield.//There are no alignments in Basic Fantasy RPG, but a Paladin must still obey a code of honor, as defined by the GM, and must try to perform duties assigned by his or her deity or religious hierarchy. If the Paladin breaks the code, all powers granted are taken away, and the character must atone for his or her actions as soon as possible. Until the Paladin successfully atones, he or she is considered an ordinary Fighter.//Paladins gain clerical spellcasting, but only starting at level 10 - until then, they may use cantrips. Paladins may also `!turn` like a cleric, though their level is considered half that of a cleric's.//Paladins radiate a constant ProtectionFromEvil (or ProtectionFromGood) aura in a 10' radius. The Paladin can also DetectEvil (or DetectGood), at will, as the spell.//Once per day, the paladin can Lay on Hands (`!loh`) to any wounded character and heal 2 points of damage, plus the Paladin's Charisma modifier. On each odd-numbered level (3rd, 5th, etc) the Paladin may do this one additional time per day (so, twice at 3rd level, three times per day at 5th level, etc.) Starting at 7th level, the Paladin may choose to cure disease (as the spell) instead of providing healing as above. At 11th level, the Paladin may also use lay on hands to neutralize poison.//Once per day, per level, a Paladin can make his or her non-magical weapon into a magic weapon for purposes of hitting creatures only able to be struck with a silver or magical weapon. This effect lasts for 1 turn (60 rounds.)

